This paper describes the development of liquid marbles with neuromorphic properties, specifically the ability to switch between high and low resistance profiles through entrainment via periodic pulses. This technology has potential applications in the development of unconventional computing devices and the study of emergent characteristics in biological neural tissue. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Other likely sub-categories include cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), cs.EM (Electromagnetism), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.CM (Computational Mathematics).
